snippet.textDisplay: What happened to cookie happened to my dog too, his name is Sam and he is a gray hound almost 1 year old at that time, he died in August of 2019 literally the month of my birthday. And many months later the January of 2020 our neighbors dog also died aka my fav dog he's name is sneaky because he likes to sneaky all the time he doesn't what to go out and he's scared, heis a black lab almost 1 year old or less he died to the same exact thing like cookies, and I cried too because we used to play all the time with Sam and sneaky  and now they're both gone but they are in the better place. snippet.textDisplay: I’m so sorry this happened to you. 🕊🤍 she will be forever missed along with your dad.  It’s hard, I remember when I lost my cat and I had this feeling of it’s not fair, because it’s not. But it’s going to get better. We took my cat to the vet and they said she had asthma, but that was weird to me. She also had a heart murmur, then she started to have what seemed like an asthma attack so we went to the hospital right away. On the way there she passed. They later found out she didn’t have asthma she had a heart condition. I miss her and everyday. Not long before we got a kitten and she missed her too. ❤️ I promise it gets better.

It startet 15 years ago and it started to get fairly stable with check-ups and treatment. 2 years ago with constant medications, the side-effects startet to show and I'm very sensitive to viruses and get sick easily. For example I had an aneurysm a few months back and I'm only 29 years old. And now with the CoVid-19 I'm locked up at home. If I'm exposed, then that's it...
